WEBVTT

00:03.119 --> 00:04.640
<i>♪ Let's go real far ♪</i>

00:04.800 --> 00:06.399
<i>♪ I should pack my bag first ♪</i>

00:06.560 --> 00:09.680
<i>♪ We've got so much to see ♪</i>

00:09.840 --> 00:11.080
<i>♪ If you really want ♪</i>

00:11.240 --> 00:12.760
<i>♪ And you really do ♪</i>

00:12.920 --> 00:16.680
<i>♪ I could go round the world with you ♪</i>

00:16.840 --> 00:19.840
<i>♪ I'll be there for you ♪</i>

00:20.000 --> 00:23.200
<i>♪ Whatever you do ♪</i>

00:23.360 --> 00:26.320
<i>♪ I'll be there with you ♪</i>

00:26.480 --> 00:28.799
<i>♪ Ollie and Moon ♪</i>

00:32.920 --> 00:36.480
[beatboxing]

00:36.640 --> 00:39.360
[beatboxing]

00:41.919 --> 00:44.120
-Pah!
-Wow, Stanley!

00:44.280 --> 00:45.720
That's drum-tastic!

00:45.879 --> 00:47.919
I didn't know you could do that.

00:48.080 --> 00:50.760
Well, I've been practising
in my shell for a while.

00:50.919 --> 00:54.040
But now I can [beatboxing] out loud!

00:54.199 --> 00:56.480
And sign up for this!

00:56.640 --> 00:58.919
[Ollie] "The Battle of the Beats?"

00:59.080 --> 01:01.199
-It's a drumming contest.
-Cool!

01:01.360 --> 01:04.399
-Sign me up, too!
-Really? You'd drum with me?

01:04.560 --> 01:07.520
You betcha I would! Ollie, too!

01:07.679 --> 01:09.840
We'll be an all-drum band!

01:13.520 --> 01:15.880
-Hit it, Ollie!
-Me? But...

01:16.039 --> 01:18.320
-We're gonna have so much fun!
-But...

01:18.479 --> 01:19.840
There's something you should--

01:20.000 --> 01:23.479
And... we are all signed up.
No backing out now!

01:23.640 --> 01:27.440
-Yeah, Ollie? You were saying?
-I... I don't know how to drum.

01:27.600 --> 01:30.000
-What?
-Well, don't worry.

01:30.160 --> 01:31.960
You'll pick it up by tonight.

01:32.119 --> 01:34.160
-Tonight?
-Yep. That's when we play!

01:34.320 --> 01:36.240
So let's practise! Come on!

01:36.399 --> 01:38.119
[beatboxing]

01:42.920 --> 01:45.080
[clanging]

01:48.080 --> 01:50.160
Ugh! You know what?

01:50.320 --> 01:53.640
I'm having a brainstorm!
The band that won last year...

01:53.800 --> 01:55.199
Where'd they learn to drum?

01:55.360 --> 01:57.800
From Jaco the Drum Master, in Cuba.

01:57.960 --> 02:00.800
-Then that's where we're going!
-Aaah!

02:00.960 --> 02:02.640
To Cuba! Come on!

02:02.800 --> 02:04.720
But... Whoa!

02:11.039 --> 02:12.239
Whoo!

02:12.960 --> 02:14.640
Whee!

02:24.079 --> 02:27.400
[stewardess] <i>Now arriving in Cuba!</i>

02:33.120 --> 02:36.200
-Is that it?
-Yep! Jaco's music school.

02:40.239 --> 02:41.480
Yo, Daddy-o.

02:41.640 --> 02:44.959
Hi, Jaco? We were wondering
if you can help our friend,

02:45.120 --> 02:47.400
Ollie here, with a music problem.

02:47.679 --> 02:50.920
I dig music. Come on in.

02:55.720 --> 02:57.880
[Moon] -Wow!
[Stanley] -Mamma mia!

02:58.280 --> 02:59.799
Wow!

02:59.959 --> 03:03.120
OK, Daddy-o. Step one of my music system

03:03.280 --> 03:08.600
is digging that music
is everywhere, all around,

03:08.760 --> 03:11.440
and even inside you!

03:11.600 --> 03:14.239
-Really? Inside me?
-That's right!

03:14.399 --> 03:16.120
Now let's see what you got.

03:16.280 --> 03:18.079
Time to pound the tubs!

03:24.320 --> 03:26.079
[drums crash to the floor]

03:31.959 --> 03:34.040
You better take five, Jack.

03:34.200 --> 03:35.600
Sorry.

03:36.359 --> 03:38.280
That's OK, cat.

03:38.440 --> 03:44.399
Everybody's got rhythm.
We just have to find yours.

03:44.560 --> 03:48.239
Uh... But how about
we look outside for it?

03:48.399 --> 03:53.399
Where it won't be quite so loud,
or so destructive.

04:00.399 --> 04:01.679
Start us off with a beat,

04:01.839 --> 04:04.440
while I find something for Ollie to play.

04:10.320 --> 04:12.239
Hey! How are you guys doing that?

04:12.399 --> 04:15.320
I don't know.
I'm just a natural at things.

04:17.120 --> 04:22.039
All kinds of things, actually.
But especially, I think, drums.

04:22.640 --> 04:23.520
Grr.

04:23.840 --> 04:26.320
Yeah, I actually never thought
about how I do it either.

04:26.479 --> 04:28.240
Just happens naturally, I guess!

04:28.400 --> 04:29.680
[beatboxing]

04:29.840 --> 04:32.400
-Didn't even try to do that!
-Hey, Ollie.

04:32.560 --> 04:34.880
Your ears are all flat and upset like.

04:35.039 --> 04:36.760
Why are your ears all flat and upset?

04:36.919 --> 04:40.919
-No reason.
-Maybe try this udu, Ollie.

04:46.960 --> 04:49.320
-Is it supposed to do that?
-Er, no.

04:50.240 --> 04:52.000
How about this kalimba?

04:52.159 --> 04:53.680
[ugly sounds]

04:55.320 --> 04:59.640
-How'd you manage to do that?
-I don't know.

04:59.800 --> 05:03.719
I've got it, cats. A nice, simple guitar.

05:05.840 --> 05:07.440
[groans]

05:08.919 --> 05:12.760
I can't do it!
I'm not a natural at anything!

05:15.400 --> 05:16.280
Aaah!

05:17.599 --> 05:19.360
Oh, no, what are we going to do?

05:19.520 --> 05:23.000
The contest is tonight and Ollie
still can't play anything!

05:23.159 --> 05:26.479
Hmm. I have an idea.

05:35.719 --> 05:37.520
Why am I blindfolded?

05:37.680 --> 05:40.680
To focus on the sounds of nature!

05:43.280 --> 05:48.520
If you listen carefully, you'll
find the rhythm all around you.

05:48.680 --> 05:51.000
Concentrate, Daddy-o!

05:51.400 --> 05:54.680
[insects and birdsong, water flowing]

05:56.200 --> 05:58.400
The forest makes its own song.

05:58.560 --> 06:00.800
The trees and branches sway along.

06:00.960 --> 06:03.359
Feel the thunder of the waterfall.

06:03.520 --> 06:07.440
Hear the tweet of the birdies' call.

06:07.599 --> 06:09.520
[Ollie] I don't hear a rhythm.

06:10.000 --> 06:13.200
-Ollie, are you even trying?
-Yes.

06:13.359 --> 06:14.320
-Really?
-Yes!

06:14.479 --> 06:17.159
<i>-Really?</i>
<i>-Yes!</i>

06:17.320 --> 06:19.760
Then listen.

06:19.919 --> 06:23.080
[in rhythm] Tweet-tweet,
tweet-tweet-tweet. Tweet-tweet.

06:24.560 --> 06:27.840
Tweet-tweet!
Tweet-tweet-tweet. Tweet-tweet.

06:28.000 --> 06:31.440
Easy, right? What about
the woosh, woosh, woosh

06:31.599 --> 06:32.520
of the waterfall?

06:32.680 --> 06:34.320
Do you hear that, Ollie?

06:34.479 --> 06:36.719
Ollie? Where's Ollie?

06:38.080 --> 06:39.039
Oh, no!

06:39.200 --> 06:42.039
The only thing worse than having
a band member who can't drum,

06:42.200 --> 06:45.320
is <i>not</i> having a band member
who can't drum!

06:45.479 --> 06:46.440
Ollie!

06:46.599 --> 06:48.159
Ollie!

06:49.200 --> 06:50.760
<i>Ollie!</i>

06:53.400 --> 06:56.719
Concentrate...
You have to get this, Ollie!

06:56.880 --> 06:59.280
[sighs] My friends are counting on me.

06:59.440 --> 07:00.919
Why can't I hear the rhythm?

07:04.599 --> 07:05.479
Nope.

07:06.320 --> 07:07.280
Nope.

07:08.840 --> 07:10.640
Where is he?

07:10.799 --> 07:12.320
Oops! [whispers] Sorry!

07:14.440 --> 07:16.239
[gasps] Ollie's footprints!

07:16.400 --> 07:17.840
That way!

07:20.760 --> 07:23.280
[hammering]

07:25.200 --> 07:26.239
Hey, cat!

07:26.400 --> 07:27.479
Watch out, cat!

07:27.640 --> 07:29.760
-Hey, cat!
-Watch out, cat!

07:29.919 --> 07:32.280
-Hey, cat!
-Watch out, cat!

07:32.440 --> 07:34.000
Phew!

07:35.400 --> 07:37.680
Hey! I hear something.

07:37.840 --> 07:39.560
Am I getting it?

07:39.719 --> 07:41.599
<i>♪ Hey, cat. Watch out, cat </i>♪

07:44.359 --> 07:45.239
<i>♪ Hey, cat ♪</i>

07:45.400 --> 07:46.919
Where's that music coming from?

07:47.479 --> 07:50.280
Come on, cats. Let's follow our ears!

07:51.440 --> 07:53.880
[altogether] <i>♪ Hey, cat. Watch out, cat ♪</i>

07:54.039 --> 07:56.520
<i>♪ Hey, cat. Watch out, cat ♪</i>

07:56.680 --> 07:58.320
-Phew!
-Ollie?

07:59.599 --> 08:00.760
That was incredible!

08:00.919 --> 08:02.000
It was phenomenal!

08:02.159 --> 08:03.760
-It was...
-Musical!

08:03.919 --> 08:06.679
Does that mean you're ready
to help us win the contest?

08:07.159 --> 08:09.159
I... I think maybe so.

08:09.640 --> 08:12.400
Then we'd better get to it
before you run out of time!

08:15.440 --> 08:16.640
Heh! Sorry...

08:18.159 --> 08:19.880
We'll help you get started.

08:20.039 --> 08:21.799
[beatboxing]

08:21.960 --> 08:23.760
-Jump in, Ollie!
-Uh-huh.

08:23.919 --> 08:26.120
Here goes!

08:26.280 --> 08:27.640
Nope. That's not it.

08:29.039 --> 08:30.799
No, that's not it either.

08:32.240 --> 08:33.280
Argh!

08:39.039 --> 08:41.199
It's no use! I'm sorry!

08:41.360 --> 08:45.280
I'm just not like you guys! I can't do it.

08:47.000 --> 08:48.600
I really thought he had it.

08:48.760 --> 08:53.439
Me, too. And... uh-oh!
There go his ears again.

08:53.600 --> 08:55.120
What's the use?

08:55.280 --> 08:56.920
I'll never get it! Ever!

08:57.079 --> 08:59.920
-Grr!
-That's not a good look.

09:00.079 --> 09:05.040
Don't worry, cats. Jaco's still
got a few tricks up his sleeve.

09:09.400 --> 09:11.000
Hi. Wanna play with me?

09:11.160 --> 09:14.360
I can't. I'm supposed to be practising.

09:14.520 --> 09:16.480
Aw, come on. Can't you take a break?

09:16.640 --> 09:17.920
Just for second?

09:26.640 --> 09:29.160
I'm doing it! I'm playing music!

09:29.319 --> 09:31.120
I've really got it this time!

09:31.280 --> 09:34.000
You sure do! Thanks, sweetie.

09:34.920 --> 09:39.720
Meet my daughter.
She helps me teach sometimes.

09:39.880 --> 09:41.000
[gasps]

09:41.160 --> 09:43.720
The soccer was part of your lesson!

09:43.880 --> 09:45.520
It's my secret weapon.

09:45.680 --> 09:49.839
When you get frustrated,
you can't be educated.

09:50.000 --> 09:52.839
But after you kick the ball
around with me...

09:53.000 --> 09:55.360
You feel better! So much better!

09:55.839 --> 09:57.880
I can't believe
I didn't think of it before!

09:59.520 --> 10:00.800
Woo-hoo!

10:00.959 --> 10:04.120
<i>♪ Opposites ♪</i>
<i>♪ That's what we are ♪</i>

10:04.280 --> 10:06.000
<i>♪ We can't give up ♪</i>

10:06.160 --> 10:08.199
<i>♪ Give me a smile, say "cheese" ♪</i>

10:08.360 --> 10:11.880
<i>♪ We're buddy, buddy,</i>
<i>sing it out and shout ♪</i>

10:12.040 --> 10:16.000
<i>♪ You are my best friend,</i>
<i>we can work it out ♪</i>

10:16.160 --> 10:17.439
<i>♪ Side by side, we're ♪</i>

10:17.600 --> 10:20.400
<i>♪ Buddy, buddy, sing it out and shout ♪</i>

10:20.560 --> 10:24.640
<i>♪ Two friends together</i>
<i>is what it's all about ♪</i>

10:24.800 --> 10:27.360
<i>♪ We can work it out ♪</i>

10:27.520 --> 10:29.319
[drumming]

10:32.240 --> 10:34.640
Wow. What a show!

10:34.800 --> 10:36.720
-What style!
-What rhythm!

10:36.880 --> 10:40.439
-[bagpipes]
-[all] What a misunderstanding!

10:40.600 --> 10:43.839
I can't believe we didn't read
the whole contest title.

10:45.720 --> 10:49.280
Battle of The Beats... and Bagpipes?

10:49.439 --> 10:53.040
Well, I'll be in my shell
practising for next year!

10:54.400 --> 10:56.480
[laughter]

11:03.360 --> 11:05.360
[lively music]
